Class StandardDataFeed

java.lang.Object
  org.cougaar.qos.qrs.AbstractDataFeed
      org.cougaar.qos.qrs.StandardDataFeed
All Implemented Interfaces:
DataFeed
public abstract class StandardDataFeed
extends AbstractDataFeed

This class is provides listener support and a simple caching scheme. Despite the name, it's not particularly 'standard', in fact it's really only suitable for feeds which want to avoid calculating values on the fly, because of the expense involved. The only uses so far seem to be Remos and Erni.

Method Detail

validateKey

protected abstract boolean validateKey(java.lang.String key)
Subclass method should return true here iff the key is relevant to the subclass. If the key is not valid, the subclass will never be asked to compute a value for it.

updateValue

protected abstract DataValue updateValue(java.lang.String key)
This method does the real work of finding the current value associated with the given key. This should not usually be called as part of a query (ie from lookup, either directly or indirectly).

updateValueForKey

protected void updateValueForKey(java.lang.String key,
                                 boolean notify)
Subclasses should call this to force an update of the cache. The second arg indicates whether or not the listeners should be notified.

updateAll

protected void updateAll()
Forces and caches an update of all listener keys.

lookup

public DataValue lookup(java.lang.String key)
The query interface. A real value is returned iff the key is meaningful for this feed and a value is currently cached. No computation or updating happens here.

addListenerForKey

public void addListenerForKey(DataFeedListener listener,
                              java.lang.String key)
Add a listener for the given key. Whenever a new value for this key enters the store, all listeners will be notified. This method is part of the DataFeed interface.

removeListenerForKey

public void removeListenerForKey(DataFeedListener listener,
                                 java.lang.String key)
Remove a listener for the given key. This method is part of the DataFeed interface.
